export const articles: Article[] = [
  { id: 'land-of-dawn-guide', title: 'The Complete Guide to the Land of Dawn: MLBB Lore Explained', excerpt: 'Dive deep into the world of Mobile Legends - explore factions, regions, and the interconnected stories that make the Land of Dawn one of the richest game universes on mobile.', category: 'Lore', date: '2025-05-01', readTime: 12, author: 'Dawn Lorekeeper', tags: ['lore', 'factions', 'world-building', 'guide'], content: 'The Land of Dawn is far more than just a battlefield for heroes to clash. It is a rich, interconnected world with deep lore that spans multiple regions, each with its own culture, conflicts, and legendary heroes. Understanding this lore adds incredible depth to every match you play, transforming simple hero picks into meaningful choices aligned with the story of the world.\n\nThe Moniyan Empire stands as the largest and most powerful human civilization in the Land of Dawn. Centered around Lion Castle, this empire fields armies of knights and mages who defend against threats from the Abyss and beyond. Heroes like Tigreal, the loyal captain of the Royal Guard, and Lancelot, the greatest swordsman of the Baroque family, call this empire home. The political intrigue within the empire - especially the complex relationship between the royal family and noble houses like the Baroque - creates compelling storylines that unfold through hero interactions and special events.\n\nThe Abyss represents the greatest existential threat to the Land of Dawn. This dark dimension exists beneath the surface world, and its influence spreads like corruption. Heroes who draw power from the Abyss, like Selena and Alice, walk a dangerous line between using dark power for good and being consumed by it. The Abyss is not simply "evil" - it has its own complex hierarchy, politics, and ancient beings whose motivations are not always clear.\n\nBeyond these major powers, regions like the Agelta Desert with its ancient Djinn, the frozen North Valley home to the Ice Queen, and the Eastern Lands with their ninja clans and dragon warriors all contribute to the incredible diversity of the MLBB universe. Each region has produced heroes with unique abilities and perspectives that reflect their homeland\'s culture and challenges. Whether you are a casual player or a lore enthusiast, understanding the Land of Dawn enriches every aspect of the Mobile Legends experience.' },
  { id: 'jungle-guide-2025', title: 'Master the Jungle: Complete Jungle Guide for Season 2025', excerpt: 'From your first camp clear to late-game Lord fights - everything you need to know about jungling in Mobile Legends.', category: 'Guide', date: '2025-04-28', readTime: 15, author: 'Jungle Master', tags: ['guide', 'jungle', 'rotation', 'beginner', 'advanced'], content: 'The jungle role is the most influential position in Mobile Legends. As a jungler, you control the pace of the game, make plays across the map, and secure crucial objectives. Whether you are just starting or looking to refine your jungle game, this guide covers everything from basic clear paths to advanced macro strategies.\n\nYour jungle journey begins with the first clear. The standard 60/40 rotation means you clear the lane where your EXP laner is getting priority (60% of jungle) while leaving the remaining camps for your Gold laner (40%). Starting from the buff closest to your duo lane, clear efficiently by stacking camps and using Retribution on the buff. Time your second buff to coincide with your first gank opportunity - typically around the 1:30 mark when laners have pushed and are vulnerable.\n\nTurtle control is your most important responsibility in the early-mid game. Turtle spawns at 2:00 and respawns 2 minutes after being killed. The first Turtle provides a massive 400+ gold bonus and shield to your entire team, creating a significant gold lead. Always track the Turtle timer and position yourself 30 seconds before it spawns. Use scan or ask your roam for vision control around the pit. Lord, which spawns at 8:00 or 2 minutes after the last Turtle kill, is a pushing objective that spawns a powerful lane minion - use it to end games when you have a lead.\n\nAdvanced jungling involves understanding the concept of tempo. Good junglers don\'t just farm - they create pressure through calculated ganks, counterganks, and objective control. Learn to track the enemy jungler by checking buff spawn times and minion wave positions. If the enemy ganked top, their bot side jungle is open for counter-jungling. If your laners are pushed, look for cross-map plays on the opposite lane. The best junglers think 3 steps ahead, always considering where they will be 30 seconds from now.' },
  { id: 's-tier-heroes-may', title: 'S-Tier Heroes to Dominate Ranked (May 2025 Meta)', excerpt: 'These are the strongest heroes in the current meta. Pick any of these and your chances of winning increase dramatically.', category: 'Meta', date: '2025-05-05', readTime: 8, author: 'Meta Analyst', tags: ['meta', 'tier-list', 'ranked', 'competitive', 's-tier'], content: 'The May 2025 meta continues to favor mobile heroes with strong skirmishing potential and versatile teamfight tools. After the latest balance patch, several heroes have emerged as clearly dominant picks in both ranked and professional play. Here are the heroes that define the current meta and why you should be picking them.\n\nAmong fighters, Yu Zhong remains the undisputed king of the EXP lane. His dragon form ultimate provides incredible sustain that makes him nearly impossible to kill in extended fights. The key to playing Yu Zhong effectively is stacking your passive on jungle monsters between lane trades, then transforming at the perfect moment to survive enemy burst damage. Chou has also risen in popularity thanks to his ability to single-handedly win teamfights with well-timed kicks and ultimate grabs.\n\nIn the jungle, Ling has solidified his position as the premier assassin. His wall-climbing ability gives him unmatched map presence, allowing him to cross the map in seconds and make plays other junglers can only dream of. Hayabusa remains a strong alternative with slightly easier mechanics but equally devastating burst damage. For magic junglers, Selena provides incredible versatility with her dual-form playstyle and game-changing Abyssal Arrow stun.\n\nThe support role has been revolutionized by Mathilda, who combines incredible mobility with strong shielding and AoE damage. Her ability to dash between allies while providing utility makes her the most flexible support in the game. In the Gold lane, Brody and Claude continue to dominate as hyper-carries who can single-handedly win games from the late game. Wanwan has also emerged as a top-tier pick for mechanically skilled players who can consistently unlock her devastating ultimate barrage.' },
  { id: 'm6-recap', title: 'M6 World Championship Recap: History Made in Kuala Lumpur', excerpt: 'Relive the incredible moments from the biggest MLBB tournament ever. SRG\'s journey from underdogs to world champions.', category: 'Esports', date: '2024-12-20', readTime: 10, author: 'Esports Writer', tags: ['esports', 'm6', 'tournament', 'world-championship', 'SRG'], content: 'The M6 World Championship in Kuala Lumpur was the biggest Mobile Legends tournament ever held, featuring 24 teams from around the world competing for a record $1,000,000 prize pool. The tournament introduced the Swiss format for the first time, creating more competitive matches and surprising results throughout the group stage. From dominant performances to heartbreaking eliminations, M6 delivered unforgettable moments that will be talked about for years to come.\n\nSelangor Red Giants (SRG) entered the tournament as contenders but not necessarily favorites. Their journey through the Swiss stage was impressive but not dominating, with several close series that tested their resolve. However, once the playoff stage began, SRG transformed into a different team entirely. Their draft innovation, particularly their creative use of niche hero picks that opponents had not prepared for, became the defining characteristic of their championship run.\n\nThe grand finals against Falcons AP.Bren was a masterclass in macro play. While AP.Bren was known for their aggressive early-game style, SRG countered with disciplined farming and perfect objective control. Every teamfight was executed with surgical precision, with SRG\'s engages perfectly timed to catch AP.Bren out of position. The series went the full distance, with SRG eventually winning 4-3 in one of the closest grand finals in MLBB history. The final game was decided by a perfectly executed Lord steal that led to a base race ending in SRG\'s favor.\n\nBeyond the gameplay, M6 was significant for the growth of MLBB esports globally. Viewership numbers shattered previous records, and the tournament\'s production quality rivaled traditional sports events. The Swiss format was widely praised for creating more competitive matches and reducing the number of meaningless games. As the MLBB competitive scene continues to grow, M6 will be remembered as a turning point that elevated the esport to new heights.' },
  { id: 'hero-combos-guide', title: 'Top 10 Lethal Hero Duos That Will Wreck Enemy Teams', excerpt: 'Synergy is everything in MLBB. These hero pairings create devastating combinations that are nearly impossible to counter.', category: 'Guide', date: '2025-04-20', readTime: 9, author: 'Combo Expert', tags: ['guide', 'combos', 'synergy', 'duo', 'team-comp'], content: 'In Mobile Legends, individual hero strength matters, but hero synergy matters even more. The right duo combination can create lethal chain reactions that are nearly impossible for the enemy team to counter. Whether you are queuing with a friend or looking for heroes that pair well with your favorite main, these are the deadliest duos in the game.\n\nThe classic Franco-Lesley combo remains one of the most feared in all of MLBB. When Franco lands his hook, Lesley can immediately follow with a perfectly aligned ultimate snipe that deals devastating damage to the pulled target. At higher ranks, players know to respect this combination, which creates space for the rest of your team. The beauty of this duo is that it works at every skill level - simple concept, devastating execution.\n\nFor more advanced players, the Atlas-Vale combination is currently the most broken zone control duo in the game. Atlas pulls enemies together with his ultimate chains, grouping them into a tight cluster that Vale can hit with his maximum-width Windstorm tornado. The damage output from this combo is often enough to eliminate multiple enemy heroes in a single teamfight. The key is timing - Atlas must communicate his pull so Vale can pre-cast the tornado for maximum overlap.\n\nThe Ling-Mathilda duo represents the pinnacle of mobile play in MLBB. Both heroes have incredible mobility, allowing them to create 2v1 situations anywhere on the map. Ling\'s wall-climbing combined with Mathilda\'s shielding and AoE CC creates a persistent threat that the enemy team must constantly account for. This duo is particularly effective in the current meta because their roaming pressure can single-handedly win games through cross-map plays.' },
  { id: 'beginner-tips', title: '10 Essential Tips Every New MLBB Player Must Know', excerpt: 'Just started playing Mobile Legends? These 10 tips will save you hundreds of hours of frustration and accelerate your ranked climb.', category: 'Tips', date: '2025-04-15', readTime: 7, author: 'Coach M', tags: ['tips', 'beginner', 'new-player', 'ranked', 'basics'], content: 'Starting Mobile Legends can feel overwhelming with 130+ heroes, hundreds of items, and complex game mechanics. But don\'t worry - every pro player started exactly where you are. These 10 essential tips will help you skip the beginner mistakes and start winning games faster.\n\nFirst, master 2-3 heroes maximum. The biggest mistake new players make is trying to play every hero. Instead, pick 2-3 heroes from different roles and learn them deeply. Understand their damage output, their limits, and their power spikes. A player who has mastered one hero will almost always beat a player who has played 50 heroes casually. Start with easy heroes like Miya, Layla, or Tigreal before moving to mechanically demanding heroes like Fanny or Ling.\n\nSecond, focus on last hitting minions in your lane. Gold is the most important resource in MLBB, and last hitting ensures you get the maximum gold from each minion wave. Missing last hits means falling behind in items, which means dealing less damage, which means losing teamfights. Practice last hitting in classic mode until you can consistently get 8+ last hits per wave.\n\nThird, learn to read the minimap. The minimap is arguably the most important tool in the game. Checking it every 3-5 seconds tells you where the enemy jungler is, which lanes are pushed, and whether objectives are being contested. If you don\'t see the enemy jungler on the minimap, assume they are coming to gank you. This simple habit will dramatically reduce your death count and improve your win rate.' },
  { id: 'patch-analysis', title: 'Patch 1.8.96 Analysis: Big Changes to Tanks and Assassins', excerpt: 'The latest patch shook up the meta with significant buffs to tanks and nerfs to burst assassins. Here is what you need to know.', category: 'Patch', date: '2025-05-03', readTime: 6, author: 'Patch Analyst', tags: ['patch', 'balance', 'update', 'meta-changes', 'buffs', 'nerfs'], content: 'Patch 1.8.96 brought significant changes to the MLBB meta, most notably a comprehensive rebalancing of the tank and assassin classes. The patch aimed to address the dominance of burst-oriented assassins in the current meta while giving tanks more tools to fulfill their role as frontline initiators and protectors.\n\nTank items received substantial buffs across the board. Brute Force Breastplate now reduces physical damage by 8% (up from 6%), making it a more impactful anti-physical item. Dominance Ice received a cooldown reduction buff (now 10% at base), and Immortality\'s resurrection HP was increased from 15% to 20%. These changes make tank items significantly more gold-efficient, encouraging players to invest in survivability. The most impactful hero-specific change was Atlas receiving a cooldown reduction on his ultimate, allowing him to chain teamfight CC more frequently.\n\nAssassins took several nerfs aimed at reducing their one-shot potential. Saber\'s ultimate base damage was reduced by 8%, and Hayabusa\'s shuriken damage scaling was adjusted to favor extended fights over burst. Gusion\'s early game damage was slightly reduced, though his late game remains intact. These changes aim to make assassins more reliant on skill expression rather than raw numbers, rewarding players who master combo timing over those who simply all-in with maximum damage.\n\nThe net effect of these changes is a shift toward longer teamfights and more strategic gameplay. Tanks are now more effective at their primary role of absorbing damage and engaging, while assassins must be more selective about when and how they engage. Look for tank-support compositions to rise in popularity, and expect the meta to favor heroes who excel in extended fights over pure burst damage dealers.' },
  { id: 'emblem-guide', title: 'Complete Emblem Guide 2025: Best Builds for Every Role', excerpt: 'Your emblem setup can make or break your game. Learn the optimal emblem builds for every role in the current meta.', category: 'Guide', date: '2025-04-25', readTime: 11, author: 'Build Expert', tags: ['guide', 'emblem', 'build', 'talents', 'optimization'], content: 'Emblems are one of the most overlooked aspects of MLBB by new and intermediate players. Yet proper emblem setup can provide thousands of gold worth of stats for free, making the difference between winning and losing closely matched games. This guide covers the optimal emblem builds for every role in the 2025 meta.\n\nFor tanks, the Tank Emblem with Firmness, Tenacity, and Concussive Blast is the gold standard. Firmness provides flat defense stats that scale well into the late game, Tenacity reduces the duration of enemy crowd control allowing you to stay in fights longer, and Concussive Blast adds valuable stun utility. This combination maximizes your primary role as an initiator and damage absorber. Against heavy CC compositions, consider swapping Tenacity for Invincible if available.\n\nAssassins should always run the Assassin Emblem with Rupture, Weapons Master, and Quantum Charge. This talent combination maximizes burst damage against low HP targets. Rupture provides flat physical attack, Weapons Master ensures your damage penetrates enemy armor, and Quantum Charge adds execute damage to your skill combos. The key synergy here is that Quantum Charge triggers on your skill combo, dealing bonus damage to low HP targets precisely when you want to execute them.\n\nMarksmen benefit most from the Marksman Emblem with Agility, Bargain Hunter, and Weakness Finder. Agility provides early game attack speed that helps with last hitting, Bargain Hunter accelerates your item completion which is crucial for hyper-carries who need their core items as fast as possible, and Weakness Finder provides valuable kiting ability. The slow effect from Weakness Finder makes it nearly impossible for melee heroes to reach you, dramatically improving your survivability in teamfights.' },
  { id: 'esports-teams-guide', title: 'Meet the Top MLBB Pro Teams of 2025', excerpt: 'From Blacklist International to ONIC Esports - get to know the teams dominating professional Mobile Legends play.', category: 'Esports', date: '2025-04-30', readTime: 8, author: 'Esports Analyst', tags: ['esports', 'teams', 'pro-play', 'competitive', 'M-series'], content: 'The MLBB professional scene has grown exponentially, with teams from Southeast Asia, the Middle East, and Latin America competing at the highest level. Understanding the top teams and their playstyles gives you valuable insights into the professional meta that you can apply to your own ranked games.\n\nBlacklist International from the Philippines remains one of the most decorated organizations in MLBB esports. Known for their disciplined macro play and innovative draft strategies, Blacklist has consistently been a top contender at every M-Series tournament. Their coaching staff is considered among the best in the business, consistently finding creative hero picks that catch opponents off guard. Their signature playstyle revolves around perfect objective control and teamfight execution, rarely making unforced errors.\n\nONIC Esports, representing Indonesia, has built a reputation for aggressive, fast-paced gameplay that overwhelms opponents. Their junglers are known for early-game invades and relentless ganking pressure that snowballs advantages quickly. While their aggressive style can sometimes lead to spectacular throws, when executed properly it creates games that feel over before they begin. ONIC\'s dedication to aggression has made them fan favorites and consistently dangerous in international competition.\n\nThe rise of Middle Eastern teams has been one of the most exciting developments in MLBB esports. Teams like Team Falcons have shown that the region can compete at the highest level, with incredible individual talent and rapidly improving team coordination. The investment in MLBB esports infrastructure in the Middle East suggests this region will continue to produce increasingly competitive teams in the years to come.' },
  { id: 'skins-collection', title: 'Best MLBB Skins of All Time: Must-Have Collections', excerpt: 'From legendary to collector edition - these are the most beautiful and iconic skins in Mobile Legends history.', category: 'Meta', date: '2025-04-18', readTime: 7, author: 'Skin Collector', tags: ['skins', 'cosmetics', 'collection', 'collector', 'legendary'], content: 'Mobile Legends has released hundreds of skins since its launch, ranging from basic recolors to jaw-dropping Collector Edition masterpieces. While skins don\'t affect gameplay (except for a small stat bonus), collecting them is one of the most enjoyable aspects of the MLBB experience. Here are the must-have skins that every serious player should consider adding to their collection.\n\nCollector Edition skins represent the pinnacle of MLBB cosmetic design. These ultra-rare skins feature completely new animations, voice lines, and visual effects that transform the hero into something entirely different. Alucard\'s Lightborn Striker Collector skin is widely considered the best Collector in the game, with stunning golden armor and completely reimagined skill effects. Kagura\'s Soryu Maiden Collector transforms her into a dragon goddess with breathtaking visual effects. These skins are expensive but offer the most dramatic visual transformations.\n\nEpic skins offer excellent visual upgrades at a more accessible price point. Lancelot\'s Rose Knight, Gusion\'s Dual Blade, and Fanny\'s Skylark are among the most popular Epic skins in the game. Each features new animation sets, enhanced visual effects, and unique recall animations that make them stand out in any match. For players who want impressive-looking skins without the Collector Edition price tag, Epic skins provide the best value.\n\nSpecial and Elite tier skins are the bread and butter of most collections. While they don\'t feature the dramatic transformations of higher tiers, many Special skins are genuinely beautiful and well-designed. The Zodiac Series, Festival Series, and Nation Series have produced some of the most creative skin designs in MLBB, with unique themes that celebrate different cultures and traditions from around the world.' },
];

